Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.97,0:03:31.84,Song,,0,0,0,,{\q2\fade(900,0)\c&HFFFFFF&\bord0\shad3\blur1\4c&H5DBF63&\b1\fnHitch Hike\fs65\pos(310,10)\3c&HD0BFA9&}Episode 23\N {\fs120}\N\N\NTime
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.94,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Five years ago,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.84,0:03:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I succeeded my grandfather, \Nbecoming the owner of Slothium.{/inherited the position of Slothium's owner from my grandpa}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.08,0:03:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to see{/ascertain} with my own eyes as you wander alone \Nthrough the wasteland{/heath} to meet your fate{/towards your final days}.{this line made my lose my marbles, I am utterly and completely lose as to when did she want this, why and what does this imply}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.35,0:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.05,0:03:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured it out right away -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.02,0:03:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we are two disbelievers in the eternal love, \Ncut from the same cloth.{/we are alike, both don't believe ... }{I'm fed up with this gibberish monologue full of leading-nowhere sophistry}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I'm wandering \Nthrough that same wasteland myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.40,0:03:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryo...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.60,0:04:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What lies ahead of this place{/of now}... \NWhat lies ahead of my life...{unsure, maybe "what lies ahead for me in my life", not "after it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.31,0:04:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of future...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, neither can break away from the other.{I have no idea what this Ippon may mean in pachislot, looking up brought a meaning of "1000 yen" so I assumed "neither of them can gain more than a 1000 coins of advantage over the other" though it's probably wrong and actually it's something like "look, neither can draw an ippon combo" or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.12,0:04:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an even{/equal} battle again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Superb!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I even doing?{At this point, I don't even expect them to be consequtive, it's just some random dramatic line followed by a whole lot of nothing, I have no idea why is he asking this here, no fucking reason} At last... At last, I was given \Na chance to put into practice my resolve to fight Daiba.{/Even though I said I'm fully prepared to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Aligned?{rather "Completed/prepared" but I want a better flow with "line" in the second clause} However, even now, \NI still can't see a thing beyond this line{/moment}.{I must have lost my translation competence completely, for I can't make heads or tails of what they say for god knows how many lines in a row, so I'll just mark those with wtf now - wtf}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Pachislot machine, Yozakura Seven, Slothium, \NI won't spare my life{/put my everything on the line} to get the answer!{wtf - the relation to "answer" is unclear, maybe "I'll bet my everything on the answer" and who tf knows who is answering who and what's the question}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:05:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To pull it out of you, even by force!{wtf - Lit: draw conclusion/deduce}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.67,0:05:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, the Ultimate King \Ncan even press with his eyes shut?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He really does!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.84,0:05:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But how can that be...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't see. Even when I combust my life \Nto 100% of its capacity, what lies beyond that line...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.58,0:05:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This manner of pressing \Nis different from Daiba's usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.19,0:05:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened there, Ginya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.92,0:05:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Must defeat... Must defeat Daiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For now, I have no other means \Nfor answering Daiba, but to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.93,0:05:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of thoughts is Daiba having,{I'm sure about "press" but "thinking" sounds rather like "is having" so I combined, even though both make little sense} \Npressing the buttons now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.53,0:05:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Daiba doesn't look my way anymore{/at me}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make you turn your face to me \Nonce again, Daiba Ryo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.24,0:05:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryo, who desired so much to fight Otonashi \Ndoesn't even look his way now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.21,0:05:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't ever turn to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like Ryo is going to some place I don't know, \Nto some place away, out of hand's reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.12,0:06:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi! \NAfter this one,{added} start building{/collect/complete/align} a Big!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.70,0:06:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.17,0:06:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull Ryo back to reality{added},{maybe "don't let ryo stray away"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.86,0:06:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.54,0:06:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Owner, get yourself together{/calm down}! \NWhat happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.77,0:06:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted{sounds rather like present tense} to see it - Ryo driven to the life's edge{/balancing between life and death}.{this girigiri may mean all sorts of things here, none of which make any sense provided owner cares about ryo at least a bit} \NBut now... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I first met Ryo, \NI should've gone upfront about it.{wtf} Why did I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did I ever greenlight such a match?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.82,0:06:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Owner...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.02,0:06:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get closer... Please... \NDon't look at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.19,0:06:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't run away, Owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Aoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.09,0:06:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The duty is yours{/you're obliged} to witness, until the conclusion, \Nthe fight between these two men!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.14,0:06:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use covering your eyes.\NThe clatter{/clash} of their fight would still reach your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.97,0:06:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you cover your ears, \Nyou would still smell the fragrance of their fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you try to repulse{/reject from the outside} it with your whole body, \Nyour heart would still feel what's going on.{/won't allow that}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.08,0:07:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Both you and me came to this fight \Nperfectly aware of it.{/have accepted it would be that kind of fight}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.90,0:07:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What I want to see, what I want to learn, \Nwhere I want to go...{wtf}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.57,0:07:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After making it this far, \Nwhy do I suddenly feel lost?{/Having made it all the way here, what is this feeling of having lost my way/hesitation}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Ultimate King, \NI had to defeat numerous rivals along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I looking for \Nin this final battle of my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.72,0:07:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see.{guess, maybe "watch this"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What... What is this light now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.29,0:07:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.13,0:07:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Ryo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.74,0:07:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Otonashi Ginya, you were chosen \Nby the Ultimate King himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.31,0:08:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Align the Big now! Please! \NIt should be easy for you!{/You should be able to}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.61,0:08:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want Daiba... \NI want Daiba to return to reality!{he uses that "pull back" thing again and actually says "I want to pull daiba ..." but I don't see a way to have both this and two "daibas" in one line}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.62,0:08:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya understands that too, Owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the only one in agony now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean!{/not the matter/not about that} \NHaven't you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryo is fighting \Nin a whole another world, alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.96,0:08:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The place that he yearned for \Nis a completely different battlefield!{wtf}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.97,0:08:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't you notice \Nsomething bizarre in Daiba's appearance{/state}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.97,0:08:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? \NHe is laughing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya, you're the only one \Nwho can pull Daiba back to our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.09,0:08:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it...{/It's this way... (guess)}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.96,0:08:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, Big!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.86,0:08:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nailed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.75,0:09:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.84,0:09:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I heard it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of your burning life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.31,0:09:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of burning life?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.18,0:09:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A warm, gentle and embracing{/enveloping} motion.{added}{wtf - he was talking about sounds just now, and then he suddenly switches to "action/conduct"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the depths of the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.89,0:09:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it's quiet{/calm} and docile{I intoduced "action; conduct; behaviour;" two lines before so I omit it here.}. \NAnd yet, immense in strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.09,0:09:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbinding{/liberating}.{Lit: gives rein to one's imagination}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.70,0:10:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{It's as though this motion }Originating from the Earth's womb, \Njust like magma.{deliberate mistranslation here: he says "like a magma, erupting/spouted out ..." but my variant sounds cooler + it's unclear if it's magma or feeling is spouted in his wording}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.66,0:10:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A potent motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.90,0:10:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I heard it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This sound that a life makes \Ncame clearly to me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.41,0:10:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the sound of Daiba's life burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.41,0:10:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \NThat's a relief.{/I'm grateful}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Daiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.75,0:10:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things are{added to aid the flow of speech} once-in-a-lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.33,0:10:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Like our meeting.{/meeting you} \NNo, everything{ that has been} up to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.03,0:10:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Time will always be the same.{wtf - what did he mean to say by this, I don't know, it contradicts the prev line and Lit is "the time is the same again, too"; my guess is "the time is unaltering/persistent/imperceptible => the same" or rather "we happened to spend our lives in the same time"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.10,0:10:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is continuous{/concatenated}, \Nforming an endless flow of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally, times intersect{/overlaps/heaps up}, \Ncreating history{/memories}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.94,0:10:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By shredding{/mincing}{in the last "jikai" gin said that like "we engrave the memories in the time" but here it's a slightly different wording and completely deviating meaning already} the past, \Nwe create the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This fight of ours \Nalso exists on the intersection{/overlapping} of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.34,0:10:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, though it saddens me{/however lamentable/even if it's sad}, \Nthis intersection is only transient.{/time is not eternal/cannot last forever - this a bit weird way to put it, but that's how he says it}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Because time{added for more consistency with his catchphrase} is not something you can stop.{/and you can't stop it}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.15,0:10:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case... \NIn that case, I must exceed my limits to stop it.{Lit: "Then I will bring it to stop" which is nowhere as colorful and emotional as what I made up}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.52,0:11:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By burning my everything \Ninside this one moment, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.49,0:11:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My finger will stop the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.25,0:11:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Daiba Ryo, your capacities are well and truly \Nbeyond any ordinary man's.{wtf, lit: "Daiba ryo, a man of that name, what kind of man is he?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.06,0:11:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as those in your possession, Ginya.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.13,0:11:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of burning lives of those two \Nreaches me even down here!{/I can hear even this far, up to here}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It heats me thoroughly, to the very core!{/Lit: all the way to my heart, it makes me hotter}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.07,0:11:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You once told me this,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In a country, spared by{/without} wars and revolution,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.37,0:11:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what{/where} is this place where{/for ... to} men \Ncan fight with their lives on the line?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.51,0:11:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In all my time, \NI never looked at the opponent I'm fighting with.{wtf - he rather says "in my days/era, I couldn't see ..." but this makes no fucking point, also jidai may be "gimmick/right of a stronger/handwriting" which makes even less sense, so my bet is "in all my career, I always played my own game, without sightseeing" because that's pretty much every daiba's game we've seen}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.85,0:11:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, rather, even to this day, \NI just never cared enough to go out of my way.{this is even more [wtf] than prev line, lit "maybe/there's no telling if up to now I didn't ascertain/make sure" so my bet is "none of my previous opponents were worth my attention [to their score/character], therefore I just won with my eyes on the machine, except this one time"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.02,0:12:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.82,0:12:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What a willpower{/kind of man}, even in his condition{/with that body}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginya, I had to realize it with my own heart.{/lit: noticed in my heart - no idea what she noticed or why is she saying this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.80,0:12:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good, just being able to fight you like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.01,0:12:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm happier by just thinking \Nhow we got to experience{/live through} the same moment together.{/Lit: both are able to feel/sense the same time/period - this brings me happy thoughts}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The time... \NOne is powerless to{/cannot} stop the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.35,0:12:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But this one moment I'm living through \Ntogether with Daiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.49,0:12:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a lifetime... The answers \Nto everything I have ever lived for, are here.{this wording is horrendous but I'm too fed up, none of the lines make sense: "I lived, everything's answers are here"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.96,0:12:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a lifetime...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.86,0:12:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What me and Daiba have once met for \Nis this one fight!{/this fight between ... is why we met}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.94,0:12:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why I met Oumi,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,why I met Teresa...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.97,0:13:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why I had met, but also parted \Nwith all those {various }people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.41,0:13:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was{/took place} just for this day{added} alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.01,0:13:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Otonashi. \NEverything I have or ever had...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.42,0:13:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm throwing at you \Neven more than that! So you, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.92,0:13:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm savouring{/enjoying} it, Daiba. \NThis one moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.16,0:13:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,From approximately 8000 winning combinations{/arrangements/alignments}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.83,0:13:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm aiming for one and only{/I only choose one}, \Njust for this moment's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.41,0:13:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason the two of us had met...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Was for this one, \Nonce-in-a-lifetime battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.14,0:13:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! His reels are exactly like Otonashi's!{guess, I hear something resembling "reel" there, though it's vague and is rather "look at otonashi's ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.65,0:13:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.72,0:13:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They are aiming{/building/arranging/aligning} for the same pattern after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.29,0:13:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord3}This time, it's Daiba who is chasing Otonashi.{/it's Otonashi who Daiba's after}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:13:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you even believe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.04,0:14:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Astonishing. \NThis can't be a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.34,0:14:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Both are aiming for the same titles{i'm not sure what "me" stands for here, would assume it's titles and their positions combination on the display}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Remaining time: 1 hour 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.12,0:14:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Daiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.16,0:14:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that how much strength he needs \Nto endure the pain to fight{added, this was intended in []} me?{/is he coping with the pain to that extent of power}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.13,0:14:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Worries aside, keep going forward, Otonashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.83,0:14:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I should, Daiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.47,0:14:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.23,0:14:59.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Remaining time: 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.26,0:15:07.27,Song,,0,0,0,,Update on the scores: \NKing Daiba Ryo - 45 678 coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.00,0:15:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Fingers too... \NThe thumb is going numb already.{/I'm losing the sensation in the thumb}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.60,0:15:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But considering what Daiba is going through, \Nthis is bullshit!{/But compared to Daiba's pain, this much...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.77,0:15:13.88,Song,,0,0,0,,Challenger Otonashi Ginya - 43 569 coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NI can't see your hand moving.{/Your hand stopped already?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.81,0:15:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing I stop today is time. \NAnd I'm not yet finished!{/Don't get ahead of yourself!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.45,0:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.51,0:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.89,0:15:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, secured it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.83,0:15:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Remaining time: 1 minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Update on the scores: \NKing Daiba Ryo - 51 366 coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.04,0:15:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Challenger Otonashi Ginya - 51,381 coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.57,0:15:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With a lead of only 15, \NOtonashi is going to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.84,0:15:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about winning or losing anymore.{/the outcome of the battle doesn't matter anymore}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whichever way this battle ends!{/I don't care if it goes up or down}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This life...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,My life...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.99,0:15:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept it,{/I'm giving it to you/inherit it (i'm really unsure how to make this sound the coolest)}
